    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Direct positive paper produces black-and-white positive prints directly without relying on the film negative in the print's production. It is coated with a silver gelatin emulsion for reversible emulsion and has been used primarily for pinhole photography.</Note_Text>
